WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.085 --> 00:00:03.044
[Boyd] <i>Previously on</i> From...

2
00:00:03.045 --> 00:00:05.797
Everybody here just talks about
how afraid they are of dying.

3
00:00:05.798 --> 00:00:07.215
Well. I don't think
that's the worst thing

4
00:00:07.216 --> 00:00:08.299
that can happen to you here.

5
00:00:08.300 --> 00:00:09.467
<i>When I blacked out in the ruins.</i>

6
00:00:09.468 --> 00:00:11.761
<i>it was almost like
I went somewhere.</i>

7
00:00:11.762 --> 00:00:13.221
<i>And then I heard those children.</i>

8
00:00:13.222 --> 00:00:16.224
- They were screaming that word.
- Anghkooey.

9
00:00:16.225 --> 00:00:18.560
[Jade] <i>The bottle tree
was important to Miranda.</i>

10
00:00:18.561 --> 00:00:19.811
<i>She had visions of these trees.</i>

11
00:00:19.812 --> 00:00:22.147
Somewhere in these numbers
is a key

12
00:00:22.148 --> 00:00:23.940
to something
that we need to understand.

13
00:00:23.941 --> 00:00:25.525
There is no baby.

14
00:00:25.526 --> 00:00:27.902
Yes. there is.
It's just not yours.

15
00:00:27.903 --> 00:00:29.738
[Fatima crying]
Elgin. please!

16
00:00:29.739 --> 00:00:31.698
Fatima is missing.

17
00:00:31.699 --> 00:00:33.950
[Donna] What we're asking for
is a search party.

18
00:00:33.951 --> 00:00:37.620
What if Fatima is out
doing something to help us?

19
00:00:37.621 --> 00:00:39.206
I think she's gonna be okay.

20
00:00:41.417 --> 00:00:44.335
The last place we saw her
was out at the shack.

21
00:00:44.336 --> 00:00:45.670
which is about here.

22
00:00:45.671 --> 00:00:48.548
So. we've got people
covering this whole area

23
00:00:48.549 --> 00:00:51.676
in and around town.
which leaves here. here.

24
00:00:51.677 --> 00:00:53.179
What was she doing?

25
00:00:55.431 --> 00:00:56.348
- What?
- [door opens]

26
00:00:56.349 --> 00:00:58.558
Out at the... shack.

27
00:00:58.559 --> 00:01:00.310
- Why was she out there?
- [door closes]

28
00:01:00.311 --> 00:01:01.437
Hey.

29
00:01:02.938 --> 00:01:04.190
I think Elgin knows.

30
00:01:07.318 --> 00:01:08.735
I think
he knows where Fatima is.

31
00:01:08.736 --> 00:01:11.614
[ominous music playing]

32
00:01:23.083 --> 00:01:24.585
[grunting]

33
00:01:26.295 --> 00:01:27.213
[grunting]

34
00:01:31.801 --> 00:01:32.718
[clattering]

35
00:01:34.428 --> 00:01:35.595
[inhales sharply]

36
00:01:35.596 --> 00:01:39.891
[groaning]

37
00:01:39.892 --> 00:01:42.853
[breathing heavily]

38
00:01:44.438 --> 00:01:47.440
[groaning]

39
00:01:47.441 --> 00:01:52.487
[crying]

40
00:01:52.488 --> 00:01:55.991
[breathing heavily]

41
00:01:58.369 --> 00:02:01.247
[screaming]

42
00:02:03.415 --> 00:02:05.416
[screaming]

43
00:02:05.417 --> 00:02:08.003
["Que Sera. Sera (Whatever Will
Be. Will Be)" plays]

44
00:02:16.679 --> 00:02:21.474
<i>♪ When I was just a little boy ♪</i>

45
00:02:21.475 --> 00:02:23.852
<i>♪ I asked my father ♪</i>

46
00:02:23.853 --> 00:02:25.604
<i>♪ "What will I be?" ♪</i>

47
00:02:27.731 --> 00:02:29.983
{\an8}<i>♪ "Will I be handsome?" ♪</i>

48
00:02:29.984 --> 00:02:32.610
{\an8}<i>♪ "Will I be rich?" ♪</i>

49
00:02:32.611 --> 00:02:36.573
<i>♪ Here's what he said to me ♪</i>

50
00:02:36.574 --> 00:02:39.951
<i>♪ Que sera sera ♪</i>

51
00:02:39.952 --> 00:02:43.956
<i>♪ Whatever will be will be ♪</i>

52
00:02:45.708 --> 00:02:49.752
<i>♪ The future's not ours to see ♪</i>

53
00:02:49.753 --> 00:02:52.590
<i>♪ Que sera sera ♪</i>

54
00:02:54.884 --> 00:02:57.720
{\an8}<i>♪ What will be will be ♪</i>

55
00:03:07.396 --> 00:03:12.025
{\an8}<i>♪ Now I have
children of my own ♪</i>

56
00:03:12.026 --> 00:03:14.527
{\an8}<i>♪ They ask their father ♪</i>

57
00:03:14.528 --> 00:03:18.072
<i>♪ "What will I be?" ♪</i>

58
00:03:18.073 --> 00:03:20.700
<i>♪ "Will I be pretty?" ♪</i>

59
00:03:20.701 --> 00:03:23.036
{\an8}<i>♪ "Will I be rich?" ♪</i>

60
00:03:23.037 --> 00:03:26.998
<i>♪ I tell them tenderly ♪</i>

61
00:03:26.999 --> 00:03:30.627
<i>♪ Que sera sera ♪</i>

62
00:03:30.628 --> 00:03:35.506
<i>♪ Whatever will be will be ♪</i>

63
00:03:35.507 --> 00:03:40.345
<i>♪ The future's not ours to see ♪</i>

64
00:03:40.346 --> 00:03:43.974
<i>♪ Que sera sera ♪</i>

65
00:03:45.517 --> 00:03:48.812
<i>♪ What will be will be ♪</i>

66
00:03:50.189 --> 00:03:52.690
<i>♪ Que sera sera ♪</i>

67
00:03:52.691 --> 00:03:55.653
♪

68
00:04:07.623 --> 00:04:11.876
He said she was fine and that
this was all important.

69
00:04:11.877 --> 00:04:13.586
He was so calm about it.

70
00:04:13.587 --> 00:04:14.880
He said I shouldn't be afraid.

71
00:04:16.840 --> 00:04:19.926
Look. I don't know
if he just snapped

72
00:04:19.927 --> 00:04:21.761
or if something here
is actually talking to him.

73
00:04:21.762 --> 00:04:24.055
Where is he now?

74
00:04:24.056 --> 00:04:25.431
Colony House.

75
00:04:25.432 --> 00:04:28.559
You two go up there.

76
00:04:28.560 --> 00:04:30.395
And make sure he does not leave.

77
00:04:30.396 --> 00:04:33.065
- Okay. What are you gonna do?
- Just go.

78
00:04:34.733 --> 00:04:35.651
[door opens]

79
00:04:37.236 --> 00:04:40.071
[Ethan] Do you think
they found Fatima yet?

80
00:04:40.072 --> 00:04:41.781
[Jim] I sure hope so.

81
00:04:41.782 --> 00:04:43.992
[door opens]

82
00:04:43.993 --> 00:04:45.118
[clears throat]

83
00:04:45.119 --> 00:04:47.412
- [Ethan] Victor.
- [Victor] Oh.

84
00:04:47.413 --> 00:04:49.873
- What are you doing here?
- Your mom fell down.

85
00:04:51.291 --> 00:04:52.418
What?

86
00:04:55.004 --> 00:04:56.587
[door opens and closes]

87
00:04:56.588 --> 00:04:58.132
Thank you. honey.

88
00:04:59.508 --> 00:05:01.175
- What happened?
- Mm.

89
00:05:01.176 --> 00:05:02.760
- I'm okay. I'm okay.
- Yeah?

90
00:05:02.761 --> 00:05:04.137
- Yeah?
- Yeah. yeah.

91
00:05:04.138 --> 00:05:07.223
I saw the Boy in White.

92
00:05:07.224 --> 00:05:08.766
Really?

93
00:05:08.767 --> 00:05:10.143
Yeah.

94
00:05:10.144 --> 00:05:11.644
What did he say?

95
00:05:11.645 --> 00:05:13.522
- He wasn't very helpful.
- [door opens]

96
00:05:16.942 --> 00:05:19.652
- Let's go to the diner.
- I don't want to.

97
00:05:19.653 --> 00:05:21.779
Mom and Dad need to talk.
Come on.

98
00:05:21.780 --> 00:05:23.032
- Wanna come?
- No.

99
00:05:25.701 --> 00:05:27.661
Come on. I'm hungry.

100
00:05:29.038 --> 00:05:31.457
The little girl... she led us
to the root cellar.

101
00:05:33.542 --> 00:05:35.668
Victor was there.
He was really upset.

102
00:05:35.669 --> 00:05:37.587
He remembered something
about his mother

103
00:05:37.588 --> 00:05:40.048
and the night she left.

104
00:05:40.049 --> 00:05:42.509
When I hugged him...

105
00:05:44.678 --> 00:05:46.971
I felt like Miranda was there.

106
00:05:46.972 --> 00:05:48.556
What do you mean?

107
00:05:48.557 --> 00:05:50.641
I don't know how to explain it.

108
00:05:50.642 --> 00:05:54.062
but I could feel her.

109
00:05:54.063 --> 00:05:56.190
I could feel her in that room.

110
00:05:58.067 --> 00:06:01.110
And then she took me back
to the night it happened.

111
00:06:01.111 --> 00:06:03.988
the night she left her children.

112
00:06:03.989 --> 00:06:06.824
the night she went to the tree.

113
00:06:06.825 --> 00:06:08.951
So you had. like. a vision?

114
00:06:08.952 --> 00:06:11.245
No. No. no. no. no. no.

115
00:06:11.246 --> 00:06:13.540
It was not a vision.
It was more than that.

116
00:06:16.210 --> 00:06:19.670
[sighs]
Somehow. Miranda was there.

117
00:06:19.671 --> 00:06:21.215
and she was trying
to tell me something.

118
00:06:26.386 --> 00:06:27.513
We're closed!

119
00:06:30.933 --> 00:06:33.017
You're gonna wanna hear this.

120
00:06:33.018 --> 00:06:35.895
[sighs]
No offense. Jim.

121
00:06:35.896 --> 00:06:37.855
but I think I've heard
just about enough.

122
00:06:37.856 --> 00:06:41.651
Look. I'm... I'm sorry

123
00:06:41.652 --> 00:06:43.611
about the way I came
in here yesterday.

124
00:06:43.612 --> 00:06:45.071
- I shouldn't have.
- [sighs]

125
00:06:45.072 --> 00:06:47.532
I'm scared.

126
00:06:47.533 --> 00:06:50.159
Things are happening
in my family

127
00:06:50.160 --> 00:06:53.162
that I don't know how
to protect them from.

128
00:06:53.163 --> 00:06:55.249
But the truth is.
I think you might.

129
00:07:04.675 --> 00:07:06.217
I figured you might be here.

130
00:07:06.218 --> 00:07:09.637
I need you to come up
to Colony House with me.

131
00:07:09.638 --> 00:07:13.307
Elgin's been acting strange.

132
00:07:13.308 --> 00:07:16.018
From what Ellis tells me.
the kid's been

133
00:07:16.019 --> 00:07:17.895
under a lot of stress.

134
00:07:17.896 --> 00:07:20.731
plus he and Tillie were close.

135
00:07:20.732 --> 00:07:22.859
So. what happened
to her may have just...

136
00:07:22.860 --> 00:07:26.571
Yeah. I don't know.
Anyway. he told Ellis

137
00:07:26.572 --> 00:07:29.031
that Fatima and the baby

138
00:07:29.032 --> 00:07:31.909
are gonna be the reason
we all get to go home.

139
00:07:31.910 --> 00:07:33.287
Now. that sound familiar?

140
00:07:35.122 --> 00:07:36.372
What do you need me to do?

141
00:07:36.373 --> 00:07:38.958
I need you to talk to him.
make him understand

142
00:07:38.959 --> 00:07:41.210
that if he really is
talking to something here.

143
00:07:41.211 --> 00:07:43.212
its intentions aren't good.

144
00:07:43.213 --> 00:07:45.632
You of all people
understand that. okay?

145
00:07:47.176 --> 00:07:49.635
- Just remember...
- [door closes]

146
00:07:49.636 --> 00:07:52.722
Hey.
What the hell's going on?

147
00:07:52.723 --> 00:07:55.641
Ellis and Kenny are inside.
saying Elgin can't leave.

148
00:07:55.642 --> 00:07:57.351
- Where's Acosta?
- She's still out looking.

149
00:07:57.352 --> 00:08:00.354
I came back to see
if anyone found anything.

150
00:08:00.355 --> 00:08:02.064
How many people you got inside?

151
00:08:02.065 --> 00:08:04.818
I don't know. A few. Most people
are still out searching.

152
00:08:07.821 --> 00:08:09.656
I need you to clear the house.

153
00:08:12.993 --> 00:08:17.163
When she got
to the tree... [sighs]

154
00:08:17.164 --> 00:08:20.166
...she was so close.

155
00:08:20.167 --> 00:08:23.961
But one of these things
came from the woods and...

156
00:08:23.962 --> 00:08:26.047
it smiled.

157
00:08:26.048 --> 00:08:27.633
And you watched Miranda die.

158
00:08:29.092 --> 00:08:31.220
You've had visions
before. right?

159
00:08:33.180 --> 00:08:34.764
Not like this.

160
00:08:34.765 --> 00:08:36.390
It's always more like
I'm seeing something

161
00:08:36.391 --> 00:08:37.851
that shouldn't be there.

162
00:08:39.853 --> 00:08:42.271
Like. that day that I saw
the Civil War soldier.

163
00:08:42.272 --> 00:08:44.065
it's not like I was back
in the Civil War.

164
00:08:44.066 --> 00:08:45.816
This is... this is different.

165
00:08:45.817 --> 00:08:47.360
Look. you said
something interesting.

166
00:08:47.361 --> 00:08:49.153
You said that it felt
like Miranda was trying

167
00:08:49.154 --> 00:08:51.281
to tell you something.

168
00:08:55.118 --> 00:08:57.453
- I know it sounds crazy.
- [Jade] No. it doesn't.

169
00:08:57.454 --> 00:08:59.373
Not here. anyway.

170
00:09:02.960 --> 00:09:04.835
[exhales deeply]

171
00:09:04.836 --> 00:09:06.421
Okay. Um... [chuckles]

172
00:09:08.090 --> 00:09:11.342
The first law of thermodynamics

173
00:09:11.343 --> 00:09:15.429
is that energy can neither
be created nor destroyed.

174
00:09:15.430 --> 00:09:19.058
It can only change
from one form to another.

175
00:09:19.059 --> 00:09:21.143
And our thoughts.

176
00:09:21.144 --> 00:09:24.480
our memories...

177
00:09:24.481 --> 00:09:25.815
our souls.

178
00:09:25.816 --> 00:09:27.858
if you believe
in that sort of thing.

179
00:09:27.859 --> 00:09:29.403
they're made of energy.

180
00:09:31.238 --> 00:09:32.906
And that energy...

181
00:09:34.449 --> 00:09:36.158
Maybe here. that energy...
I don't know.

182
00:09:36.159 --> 00:09:39.704
maybe it lingers.

183
00:09:39.705 --> 00:09:41.747
All right. look. you... you said
it was one of those...

184
00:09:41.748 --> 00:09:44.250
those creepy kids that led you
to the root cellar. right?

185
00:09:44.251 --> 00:09:46.460
- Yeah. a little girl.
- [Jade] Okay.

186
00:09:46.461 --> 00:09:48.045
Whatever it was
Miranda showed you.

187
00:09:48.046 --> 00:09:50.881
those kids wanted you to see.

188
00:09:50.882 --> 00:09:54.261
Where were you when you
saw the little girl?

189
00:09:57.973 --> 00:09:59.933
Out by Victor's truck.

190
00:10:11.570 --> 00:10:12.487
Elgin.

191
00:10:16.033 --> 00:10:17.116
Mind if we talk
to you for a minute?

192
00:10:17.117 --> 00:10:20.119
Yeah. Okay.

193
00:10:20.120 --> 00:10:21.830
We'll go to my room.

194
00:10:23.874 --> 00:10:27.252
- I'll take that.
- Yeah.

195
00:10:31.298 --> 00:10:33.008
[Boyd] Just in there.

196
00:10:40.599 --> 00:10:41.850
[Boyd clears throat]

197
00:10:45.354 --> 00:10:47.438
Go on. Have a seat.

198
00:10:47.439 --> 00:10:49.191
Have a seat.

199
00:10:56.323 --> 00:10:58.158
Can you watch the door for me?

200
00:11:04.247 --> 00:11:06.165
I mean. it looks like you. uh.

201
00:11:06.166 --> 00:11:08.293
packed supplies
for a couple days.

202
00:11:11.088 --> 00:11:12.296
Where were you going?

203
00:11:12.297 --> 00:11:14.091
I was just...

204
00:11:16.259 --> 00:11:19.387
[Boyd] Yeah.

205
00:11:19.388 --> 00:11:21.097
I'm gonna ask you something.

206
00:11:21.098 --> 00:11:24.225
and I want you
to tell me the truth.

207
00:11:24.226 --> 00:11:26.019
Do you know where Fatima is?

208
00:11:28.480 --> 00:11:30.565
- Elgin?
- Answer the question.

209
00:11:34.236 --> 00:11:36.363
She told me not
to say anything. I just...

210
00:11:37.989 --> 00:11:41.243
I know how much
you all care about her.

211
00:11:42.702 --> 00:11:45.371
When you told me
about your mom...

212
00:11:45.372 --> 00:11:47.249
I can't even imagine
what you're going through.

213
00:11:49.167 --> 00:11:52.586
I wanted to help.
I don't want to hurt anybody.

214
00:11:52.587 --> 00:11:55.005
But you have to understand.

215
00:11:55.006 --> 00:11:57.050
what's happening is
a good thing.

216
00:11:58.343 --> 00:12:02.556
Elgin. you said she told you
not to say anything. Who is she?

217
00:12:04.474 --> 00:12:07.643
I know it sounds crazy.
but I think she's an angel.

218
00:12:07.644 --> 00:12:10.438
- Elgin. there's...
- [Elgin] She's here to help us!

219
00:12:10.439 --> 00:12:12.898
Something is happening here
that's beyond

220
00:12:12.899 --> 00:12:17.319
our ability to understand.
like in the Bible.

221
00:12:17.320 --> 00:12:19.864
People never really
understood then.

222
00:12:19.865 --> 00:12:22.408
But they had faith.

223
00:12:22.409 --> 00:12:24.160
even when it was hard.

224
00:12:24.161 --> 00:12:27.413
especially when it's hard.

225
00:12:27.414 --> 00:12:31.041
Fatima's baby is going
to save all of us.

226
00:12:31.042 --> 00:12:33.920
Hey. Elgin. I need you
to listen to me. okay?

227
00:12:37.340 --> 00:12:39.550
- There is no baby.
- That's not true.

228
00:12:39.551 --> 00:12:42.595
Kristi and Marielle did
an ultrasound in the clinic.

229
00:12:42.596 --> 00:12:44.305
And when they
pulled up the image.

230
00:12:44.306 --> 00:12:46.265
there was nothing there.

231
00:12:46.266 --> 00:12:50.978
Whatever's growing
inside her is not a child.

232
00:12:50.979 --> 00:12:53.606
The things it's done to her.
the things it's made her do...

233
00:12:53.607 --> 00:12:56.650
You don't understand.
She explained all that to me.

234
00:12:56.651 --> 00:12:58.652
Wait. The angel?

235
00:12:58.653 --> 00:13:00.030
Yes.

236
00:13:02.991 --> 00:13:04.034
[Sara] Elgin.

237
00:13:06.244 --> 00:13:11.333
The day we met. I...
told you I killed my brother.

238
00:13:13.376 --> 00:13:16.420
Do you know why that happened?

239
00:13:16.421 --> 00:13:19.340
There were voices here
that told me

240
00:13:19.341 --> 00:13:22.636
if I killed a little boy.
we would all get to go home.

241
00:13:24.596 --> 00:13:26.597
This place...

242
00:13:26.598 --> 00:13:28.307
it doesn't give.

243
00:13:28.308 --> 00:13:30.684
It takes.

244
00:13:30.685 --> 00:13:33.437
And what it's doing to you...

245
00:13:33.438 --> 00:13:35.232
But do you see how
it's different?

246
00:13:36.608 --> 00:13:38.317
No one is dying here.

247
00:13:38.318 --> 00:13:40.319
Fatima is gonna be fine.

248
00:13:40.320 --> 00:13:42.656
You don't fucking know that.
okay? You don't know that!

249
00:13:44.241 --> 00:13:48.035
Once the baby is born.
we all get to go home.

250
00:13:48.036 --> 00:13:51.664
Elgin. even if she's pregnant.

251
00:13:51.665 --> 00:13:53.290
that's still months away.

252
00:13:53.291 --> 00:13:54.960
No. It's grown.

253
00:13:56.211 --> 00:13:58.671
You should see Fatima's belly.

254
00:13:58.672 --> 00:14:00.089
- Okay. Where the fuck is she?
- No. no. no! Hey!

255
00:14:00.090 --> 00:14:01.715
- Where the fuck is she?
- I can't!

256
00:14:01.716 --> 00:14:03.217
- Kenny!
- [all shouting at once]

257
00:14:03.218 --> 00:14:04.718
- Kenny. Kenny!
- I'll fucking kill you!

258
00:14:04.719 --> 00:14:06.387
- Where is she?
- I can't! I can't!

259
00:14:06.388 --> 00:14:08.764
[Boyd] All right! All right!
Everybody out!

260
00:14:08.765 --> 00:14:10.432
- Hey! Just relax!
- Out! Out! Outside!

261
00:14:10.433 --> 00:14:11.767
[Boyd] Everybody. now!
Let's go!

262
00:14:11.768 --> 00:14:14.186
No. He knows where
she is. all right?

263
00:14:14.187 --> 00:14:16.647
- I can't just let him sit there!
- I know. I know. Just breathe.

264
00:14:16.648 --> 00:14:18.190
No. I don't need
to fucking breathe!

265
00:14:18.191 --> 00:14:21.068
- What I need is to find my wife!
- Listen to me. Listen to me.

266
00:14:21.069 --> 00:14:23.195
We're gonna find out
everything that he knows.

267
00:14:23.196 --> 00:14:25.155
I just need you to calm down.

268
00:14:25.156 --> 00:14:27.074
What he said about the baby.

269
00:14:27.075 --> 00:14:30.536
about how big Fatima's gotten.
do you think it's true?

270
00:14:30.537 --> 00:14:33.038
I don't know. Donna.

271
00:14:33.039 --> 00:14:34.499
[Sara]
He's not gonna tell you!

272
00:14:36.334 --> 00:14:38.586
I know what it's like to have
this place in your head.

273
00:14:38.587 --> 00:14:41.505
If he really believes what he's
saying is gonna save everyone.

274
00:14:41.506 --> 00:14:44.050
he's not gonna tell you
where she is.

275
00:14:47.887 --> 00:14:50.055
Where do you keep your tools?

276
00:14:50.056 --> 00:14:51.558
- Boyd.
- Where?

277
00:14:52.809 --> 00:14:56.103
The shed.
They're in the shed.

278
00:14:56.104 --> 00:14:57.187
Whoa. Boyd.

279
00:14:57.188 --> 00:14:59.732
You stay by the door.

280
00:14:59.733 --> 00:15:01.610
He doesn't come out.

281
00:15:03.236 --> 00:15:07.156
No one...
goes back in that room.

282
00:15:07.157 --> 00:15:10.076
[dramatic music playing]

283
00:15:16.207 --> 00:15:17.167
Victor.

284
00:15:19.252 --> 00:15:22.755
Uh. how are things
going with. uh. Jasper?

285
00:15:22.756 --> 00:15:26.343
Did he say anything
interesting so far?

286
00:15:28.637 --> 00:15:30.347
It's just a doll.
You were right.

287
00:15:33.683 --> 00:15:35.476
Dolls don't talk.

288
00:15:35.477 --> 00:15:37.103
Oh.

289
00:15:40.273 --> 00:15:42.858
Look. I... [sighs]

290
00:15:42.859 --> 00:15:46.111
I-I-I just wanted to say.

291
00:15:46.112 --> 00:15:49.115
I'm sorry I haven't
been more help.

292
00:15:50.617 --> 00:15:54.578
All this...
it's been a lot for me.

293
00:15:54.579 --> 00:15:56.414
But that's no excuse.

294
00:15:58.958 --> 00:16:01.336
- From now on...
- I have to show you something.

295
00:16:03.254 --> 00:16:05.547
Okay.

296
00:16:05.548 --> 00:16:07.841
It's gonna make you angry.

297
00:16:07.842 --> 00:16:09.760
It's... it's gonna
make you hate me.

298
00:16:09.761 --> 00:16:11.261
What?

299
00:16:11.262 --> 00:16:13.681
But I have to show you.

300
00:16:13.682 --> 00:16:16.142
And then we'll be done.

301
00:16:17.477 --> 00:16:18.477
Uh. done with what?

302
00:16:18.478 --> 00:16:19.895
It's this way.

303
00:16:19.896 --> 00:16:21.690
Okay. okay. okay.

304
00:16:39.457 --> 00:16:41.543
- You really gonna do this?
- [sighs]

305
00:16:44.546 --> 00:16:46.463
I don't got time for you today.

306
00:16:46.464 --> 00:16:48.340
What comes first?

307
00:16:48.341 --> 00:16:49.800
You gonna use the saw
or the hammer?

308
00:16:49.801 --> 00:16:51.885
Oh. you know what you should do?

309
00:16:51.886 --> 00:16:53.846
You should go old school.

310
00:16:53.847 --> 00:16:57.474
Get yourself some pliers and rip
his fingernails right off.

311
00:16:57.475 --> 00:16:59.435
Well. if that's what it takes.

312
00:16:59.436 --> 00:17:01.353
You really don't see
the irony. do you?

313
00:17:01.354 --> 00:17:03.480
What the fuck are you
talking about?

314
00:17:03.481 --> 00:17:05.816
Oh. I don't know.
When Fatima killed Tillie.

315
00:17:05.817 --> 00:17:07.651
you didn't even blink.

316
00:17:07.652 --> 00:17:09.653
I mean. you did everything
you could to protect her.

317
00:17:09.654 --> 00:17:10.946
You took her out to the shed.

318
00:17:10.947 --> 00:17:13.824
You lied to the people
you claim to care about.

319
00:17:13.825 --> 00:17:15.909
Hell. Kenny's
in there right now.

320
00:17:15.910 --> 00:17:17.494
He still doesn't
know what she did.

321
00:17:17.495 --> 00:17:19.581
What happened wasn't her fault.

322
00:17:23.293 --> 00:17:24.960
Okay. and tell me how that's
any different with Elgin.

323
00:17:24.961 --> 00:17:27.838
I mean. this place
got inside his head.

324
00:17:27.839 --> 00:17:30.215
made him think
he was doing something good.

325
00:17:30.216 --> 00:17:33.177
Convinced him he was
actually protecting Fatima.

326
00:17:33.178 --> 00:17:36.723
And now. you're out here getting
ready to go medieval on him.

327
00:17:38.391 --> 00:17:39.516
Bit of a double standard.
don't you think?

328
00:17:39.517 --> 00:17:41.435
It's different.

329
00:17:41.436 --> 00:17:43.270
There's nothing
I could do about Tillie.

330
00:17:43.271 --> 00:17:45.647
Oh. bullshit. Tell yourself
anything you want. Boyd.

331
00:17:45.648 --> 00:17:48.192
I mean. you...
you walk around here

332
00:17:48.193 --> 00:17:50.444
like you're some
big knight in shining armor.

333
00:17:50.445 --> 00:17:53.447
Mr. Noble Sheriff.

334
00:17:53.448 --> 00:17:55.700
Push comes to shove. you're no
different than anyone else.

335
00:17:57.410 --> 00:17:59.244
You protect what's yours.
and you fuck anyone

336
00:17:59.245 --> 00:18:01.789
who gets in your way. You were
supposed to be better than this.

337
00:18:01.790 --> 00:18:03.999
Hey. you were
supposed to be here!

338
00:18:04.000 --> 00:18:06.001
You were...

339
00:18:06.002 --> 00:18:09.421
You and I were supposed
to figure this out together!

340
00:18:09.422 --> 00:18:11.548
You were the one who went
in the fucking street

341
00:18:11.549 --> 00:18:13.008
and got his throat slit!

342
00:18:13.009 --> 00:18:14.886
So. don't you come in here
and judge...

343
00:18:16.846 --> 00:18:18.680
You don't get to judge me.

344
00:18:18.681 --> 00:18:20.766
I'm doing the best I can.

345
00:18:20.767 --> 00:18:23.269
You know there's no coming
back from this. right?

346
00:18:25.522 --> 00:18:28.441
You said that you weren't gonna
let this place break you.

347
00:18:30.318 --> 00:18:32.653
But if you do this.

348
00:18:32.654 --> 00:18:34.655
this place has won.

349
00:18:34.656 --> 00:18:40.536
And if I don't... uh...

350
00:18:40.537 --> 00:18:43.747
my daughter-in-law dies.

351
00:18:43.748 --> 00:18:46.583
Well. that's why they call it
a rock and a hard place.

352
00:18:46.584 --> 00:18:48.461
not a rock and a soft.
comfy pillow.

353
00:18:50.547 --> 00:18:54.508
You need to decide right now
who you are.

354
00:18:54.509 --> 00:18:58.972
because that's who you're
gonna be from now on.

355
00:19:20.368 --> 00:19:22.953
Someone open this door!

356
00:19:22.954 --> 00:19:24.955
Please! [sobbing]

357
00:19:24.956 --> 00:19:28.001
[panting]

358
00:19:31.421 --> 00:19:32.380
[clattering]

359
00:19:32.381 --> 00:19:35.341
[continues panting]

360
00:19:46.769 --> 00:19:49.605
- [screams]
- [shatters]

361
00:19:49.606 --> 00:19:52.567
[panting]

362
00:20:04.412 --> 00:20:06.080
[ominous music playing]

363
00:20:18.217 --> 00:20:21.095
[inhales sharply. groans]

364
00:20:22.931 --> 00:20:23.890
[panting]

365
00:20:23.891 --> 00:20:25.933
What are we doing here?

366
00:20:25.934 --> 00:20:27.976
I thought maybe
there was a reason

367
00:20:27.977 --> 00:20:30.687
they came out to you here.

368
00:20:30.688 --> 00:20:32.147
Look. The only thing
tying together

369
00:20:32.148 --> 00:20:34.942
all the crazy
that we've seen. right...

370
00:20:34.943 --> 00:20:37.861
me. you. Miranda... the...
the one point of overlap

371
00:20:37.862 --> 00:20:40.030
in all our Venn diagrams
of crazy...

372
00:20:40.031 --> 00:20:41.115
Is the children.

373
00:20:42.784 --> 00:20:44.159
Wait.
You've seen them too?

374
00:20:44.160 --> 00:20:45.744
In the cavern.

375
00:20:45.745 --> 00:20:48.038
They were laying on these...
these slabs of rock.

376
00:20:48.039 --> 00:20:49.706
saying that word.
that "Anghkooey."

377
00:20:49.707 --> 00:20:50.707
- Yeah.
- "Anghkooey."

378
00:20:50.708 --> 00:20:52.709
over and over again.

379
00:20:52.710 --> 00:20:55.003
And I looked up.

380
00:20:55.004 --> 00:20:57.757
There was this hole
in the ceiling.

381
00:21:00.259 --> 00:21:03.679
And there was this mass
of... of... of roots.

382
00:21:03.680 --> 00:21:06.098
this tangle forming
that fucking symbol.

383
00:21:06.099 --> 00:21:07.766
The roots of the tree.

384
00:21:07.767 --> 00:21:10.060
What'd you say?

385
00:21:10.061 --> 00:21:12.187
The Boy in White...
Victor heard him.

386
00:21:12.188 --> 00:21:15.565
He said when the kids
were on the stones.

387
00:21:15.566 --> 00:21:19.736
they poured their hopes into
the roots that made the symbol.

388
00:21:19.737 --> 00:21:21.656
and then those roots
became the tree.

389
00:21:22.949 --> 00:21:24.783
Is it the bottle tree?

390
00:21:24.784 --> 00:21:27.786
Uh. yeah. I think so.

391
00:21:27.787 --> 00:21:32.958
Okay. So the. uh.
creepy kids

392
00:21:32.959 --> 00:21:35.502
made a magic tree.

393
00:21:35.503 --> 00:21:39.548
And the symbol that has been

394
00:21:39.549 --> 00:21:42.135
plaguing me this whole time...
[chuckles]

395
00:21:44.053 --> 00:21:45.805
[Jade laughing]

396
00:21:49.058 --> 00:21:52.603
You could have just
fucking told me!

397
00:21:54.605 --> 00:21:55.939
- You didn't have to...
- Jade. Jade.

398
00:21:55.940 --> 00:21:57.733
No. no! I am sick...

399
00:21:57.734 --> 00:21:59.901
I am sick and tired
of getting dicked around!

400
00:21:59.902 --> 00:22:03.155
If you really want our help.

401
00:22:03.156 --> 00:22:05.866
if there is something
you need us to understand.

402
00:22:05.867 --> 00:22:08.201
you're gonna have
to do a little better.

403
00:22:08.202 --> 00:22:10.495
because we are not getting it!

404
00:22:10.496 --> 00:22:13.624
You hear me? Message is
not fucking received!

405
00:22:15.710 --> 00:22:19.629
So. we're gonna sit here.
and we're gonna wait.

406
00:22:19.630 --> 00:22:21.798
And when you decide

407
00:22:21.799 --> 00:22:24.509
that you have
something more to say

408
00:22:24.510 --> 00:22:28.513
than fucking "Anghkooey."

409
00:22:28.514 --> 00:22:29.807
you know where to find us!

410
00:22:37.565 --> 00:22:38.648
You feel better now?

411
00:22:38.649 --> 00:22:40.693
No. Not really.

412
00:22:42.820 --> 00:22:45.280
[grunting]

413
00:22:45.281 --> 00:22:47.616
[buzzing]

414
00:22:47.617 --> 00:22:50.244
- [continues grunting]
- [buzzing continues]

415
00:22:53.790 --> 00:22:58.001
[buzzing continuing]

416
00:22:58.002 --> 00:22:59.044
[grunts]

417
00:22:59.045 --> 00:23:02.006
[buzzing continues]

418
00:23:04.217 --> 00:23:07.053
[buzzing continues]

419
00:23:11.182 --> 00:23:13.016
[inhales sharply]

420
00:23:13.017 --> 00:23:14.560
[groans]

421
00:23:15.603 --> 00:23:17.187
You're not giving yourself
time to heal.

422
00:23:17.188 --> 00:23:19.856
Well. Fatima's still out there.
I can't just sit here.

423
00:23:19.857 --> 00:23:21.192
I'm gonna get some fresh gauze.

424
00:23:22.819 --> 00:23:25.570
You were really quiet
last night.

425
00:23:25.571 --> 00:23:26.822
after they brought Julie in.

426
00:23:26.823 --> 00:23:28.281
I just felt bad.

427
00:23:28.282 --> 00:23:31.201
- I mean. she's...
- [clattering]

428
00:23:31.202 --> 00:23:32.745
Uh. Randall?

429
00:23:35.706 --> 00:23:37.165
Hey. what happened
to your bandage?

430
00:23:37.166 --> 00:23:39.042
It fell off.

431
00:23:39.043 --> 00:23:41.211
Uh. where's the stuff from
the ambulance. the new stuff?

432
00:23:41.212 --> 00:23:43.213
- It's in the cabinets.
- No. not the medicine.

433
00:23:43.214 --> 00:23:45.632
The equipment.
Where did you put the equipment?

434
00:23:45.633 --> 00:23:47.217
There's a supply closet
downstairs. We...

435
00:23:47.218 --> 00:23:49.970
- Great.
- [Marielle] Randall.

436
00:23:49.971 --> 00:23:52.597
[buzzing continues]

437
00:23:52.598 --> 00:23:55.600
[grunting]

438
00:23:55.601 --> 00:23:57.310
[buzzing continues]

439
00:23:57.311 --> 00:23:58.311
[panting]

440
00:23:58.312 --> 00:24:00.856
[buzzing continues]

441
00:24:00.857 --> 00:24:02.566
[grunts loudly]

442
00:24:02.567 --> 00:24:06.069
[buzzing continues]

443
00:24:06.070 --> 00:24:06.988
[grunting]

444
00:24:06.989 --> 00:24:09.949
[buzzing continues]

445
00:24:12.285 --> 00:24:13.952
[grunting]

446
00:24:13.953 --> 00:24:15.078
[beeping]

447
00:24:15.079 --> 00:24:16.663
[grunting]

448
00:24:16.664 --> 00:24:21.168
[buzzing continuing]

449
00:24:21.169 --> 00:24:23.170
[grunting loudly]

450
00:24:23.171 --> 00:24:24.212
[buzzing continuing]

451
00:24:24.213 --> 00:24:26.756
[emitting high-pitched tone]

452
00:24:26.757 --> 00:24:27.966
[grunting]

453
00:24:27.967 --> 00:24:30.093
- Stop!
- [Randall grunting]

454
00:24:30.094 --> 00:24:31.928
- [rapid beeping]
- Hey. hey. hey!

455
00:24:31.929 --> 00:24:33.930
- [Randall grunts]
- Hey!

456
00:24:33.931 --> 00:24:36.308
I'm trying to make
it fucking stop!

457
00:24:36.309 --> 00:24:37.809
- Hey!
- [grunting]

458
00:24:37.810 --> 00:24:40.979
Hey! Look at me! Hey!

459
00:24:40.980 --> 00:24:44.232
- Look at me. Hey. hey.
- [panting]

460
00:24:44.233 --> 00:24:46.234
- You're gonna be okay.
- [panting]

461
00:24:46.235 --> 00:24:49.404
You're gonna be all right.
Come here.

462
00:24:49.405 --> 00:24:52.200
[panting]

463
00:24:58.372 --> 00:24:59.956
[door closes]

464
00:24:59.957 --> 00:25:03.793
[ominous music playing]

465
00:25:03.794 --> 00:25:05.795
No one comes upstairs.

466
00:25:05.796 --> 00:25:08.382
- Dad. just...
- Nobody comes upstairs.

467
00:25:10.051 --> 00:25:13.262
- You make sure of that. okay?
- Yeah.

468
00:25:15.264 --> 00:25:18.225
What happens next...

469
00:25:18.226 --> 00:25:21.144
that's on me.

470
00:25:21.145 --> 00:25:24.065
[footsteps ascend stairs]

471
00:25:28.861 --> 00:25:29.945
Boyd.

472
00:25:29.946 --> 00:25:32.031
Go downstairs now. Kenny.

473
00:25:33.241 --> 00:25:35.825
We should talk to him again.

474
00:25:35.826 --> 00:25:37.994
Look. He's a good kid.

475
00:25:37.995 --> 00:25:40.121
and there's gotta be a way
to make him understand this.

476
00:25:40.122 --> 00:25:42.290
Fatima's out there.

477
00:25:42.291 --> 00:25:44.043
She may be running out of time.

478
00:25:46.921 --> 00:25:47.922
Go downstairs.

479
00:25:50.841 --> 00:25:51.759
Please?

480
00:25:51.760 --> 00:25:54.720
[ominous music playing]

481
00:26:15.283 --> 00:26:16.242
[door closes]

482
00:26:19.912 --> 00:26:21.372
I can't tell you.

483
00:26:22.873 --> 00:26:25.918
I wish I could. but...
but I can't.

484
00:26:27.086 --> 00:26:28.212
I understand.

485
00:26:30.006 --> 00:26:32.257
You need to do what
you need to do.

486
00:26:32.258 --> 00:26:34.384
Now I need to do
what I need to do.

487
00:26:34.385 --> 00:26:35.720
[thuds]

488
00:26:40.224 --> 00:26:41.434
[clatters]

489
00:26:43.352 --> 00:26:46.439
[grunting]

490
00:26:57.450 --> 00:26:58.743
[under breath] Motherfucker.

491
00:27:02.246 --> 00:27:04.290
[camera shutter clicks. whirs]

492
00:27:06.000 --> 00:27:09.836
That's how
she sends me messages.

493
00:27:09.837 --> 00:27:11.171
I think she wants
to talk to you.

494
00:27:11.172 --> 00:27:14.133
[dramatic music playing]

495
00:27:32.068 --> 00:27:33.443
Here.

496
00:27:33.444 --> 00:27:34.487
Okay.

497
00:27:39.575 --> 00:27:41.409
Victor. where are we going?

498
00:27:41.410 --> 00:27:43.370
We're here.

499
00:27:43.371 --> 00:27:44.997
We're here?

500
00:27:58.302 --> 00:28:00.512
What is that?

501
00:28:00.513 --> 00:28:02.098
I tried to make it pretty.

502
00:28:04.600 --> 00:28:06.060
The way she would have liked it.

503
00:28:07.561 --> 00:28:08.521
Hmm? Wait.

504
00:28:10.064 --> 00:28:11.482
This is where I buried Mom.

505
00:28:13.234 --> 00:28:15.361
I thought you'd want to see.

506
00:28:21.575 --> 00:28:23.035
Oh. God.

507
00:28:25.413 --> 00:28:27.540
[gasps]

508
00:28:30.709 --> 00:28:31.877
[gasps]

509
00:28:34.547 --> 00:28:36.215
Oh. God.

510
00:28:38.259 --> 00:28:39.385
[Henry exhales deeply]

511
00:28:50.062 --> 00:28:51.397
Is that...

512
00:28:53.357 --> 00:28:55.233
Is that Eloise?

513
00:28:55.234 --> 00:28:57.903
I think so.

514
00:29:01.323 --> 00:29:02.908
All I found were pieces.

515
00:29:06.036 --> 00:29:06.996
[whimpering]

516
00:29:06.997 --> 00:29:09.123
She was so small.

517
00:29:11.250 --> 00:29:13.251
There wasn't much left.

518
00:29:13.252 --> 00:29:16.463
[breathing unsteadily]

519
00:29:16.464 --> 00:29:19.007
It was my fault.

520
00:29:19.008 --> 00:29:21.050
What?

521
00:29:21.051 --> 00:29:23.553
I thought Jasper
told Christopher the secrets.

522
00:29:23.554 --> 00:29:25.597
It wasn't Jasper.
It was the Boy in White.

523
00:29:25.598 --> 00:29:28.224
I was wrong.
He told Christopher about...

524
00:29:28.225 --> 00:29:30.936
about the children and the tree.

525
00:29:34.190 --> 00:29:36.524
[crying] But I was the one
that told Mom.

526
00:29:36.525 --> 00:29:38.943
[Victor crying]

527
00:29:38.944 --> 00:29:42.197
I told her that the tree would
bring her to the children.

528
00:29:42.198 --> 00:29:45.241
[sniffling] I was the reason
that she left that night. Dad.

529
00:29:45.242 --> 00:29:50.079
- I was the reason that she died.
- Victor. you know...

530
00:29:50.080 --> 00:29:51.664
If I'd just not said anything.

531
00:29:51.665 --> 00:29:54.584
she would still be here.
and Eloise would still be here.

532
00:29:54.585 --> 00:29:58.171
No. Victor.
you were just a boy. You...

533
00:29:58.172 --> 00:29:59.547
I should have died
that night. too.

534
00:29:59.548 --> 00:30:01.257
What?

535
00:30:01.258 --> 00:30:03.343
And you should
pretend that I did.

536
00:30:03.344 --> 00:30:05.345
You don't have to be
my dad anymore.

537
00:30:05.346 --> 00:30:06.554
No. Wait. Stop.

538
00:30:06.555 --> 00:30:08.599
Goddamn it! I said stop!

539
00:30:10.059 --> 00:30:12.602
You don't ever say that again!

540
00:30:12.603 --> 00:30:15.104
Do you hear me?!

541
00:30:15.105 --> 00:30:16.232
You don't ever...

542
00:30:17.691 --> 00:30:20.527
I'm your dad.

543
00:30:20.528 --> 00:30:23.530
I will never stop
being your dad.

544
00:30:23.531 --> 00:30:27.116
Your mother did what she did
because she loved you.

545
00:30:27.117 --> 00:30:28.326
[whimpering]

546
00:30:28.327 --> 00:30:30.286
She was trying to protect you.

547
00:30:30.287 --> 00:30:32.121
[sniffling]

548
00:30:32.122 --> 00:30:33.748
That's my job now.

549
00:30:33.749 --> 00:30:36.084
Okay?

550
00:30:36.085 --> 00:30:37.503
That's my job.

551
00:30:40.839 --> 00:30:42.257
Okay?

552
00:30:42.258 --> 00:30:45.553
[dramatic music plays]

553
00:30:49.056 --> 00:30:50.682
[Jade] Listen. If those
kids made the tree.

554
00:30:50.683 --> 00:30:53.518
then those messages
in the bottles. the numbers.

555
00:30:53.519 --> 00:30:55.603
they have to matter.

556
00:30:55.604 --> 00:30:57.647
How do we know the numbers
mean anything?

557
00:30:57.648 --> 00:31:00.483
We don't even know who
put them there.

558
00:31:00.484 --> 00:31:02.652
I mean. think of all the people
who have been here.

559
00:31:02.653 --> 00:31:05.196
We could be chasing
someone's random delusion.

560
00:31:05.197 --> 00:31:08.533
No! Miranda knew
those bottles were important.

561
00:31:08.534 --> 00:31:11.244
Why else would she have
a replica in her backyard?

562
00:31:11.245 --> 00:31:13.580
She's right. Like. there's
something there. There has

563
00:31:13.581 --> 00:31:15.540
- to be something there.
- Of course. There has to be.

564
00:31:15.541 --> 00:31:17.333
All right. Okay.
There's ten numbers. right?

565
00:31:17.334 --> 00:31:20.211
- Two are backwards?
- Yes. the two and the sevens.

566
00:31:20.212 --> 00:31:22.005
Great.
So that means there's 12.

567
00:31:22.006 --> 00:31:23.381
And believe me. I have tried

568
00:31:23.382 --> 00:31:26.801
every mathematical.
astronomical. astrological.

569
00:31:26.802 --> 00:31:30.346
Babylonian 12-point numerical
cipher I can imagine.

570
00:31:30.347 --> 00:31:33.391
The Zodiac. months of the year.
fucking eggs in a carton.

571
00:31:33.392 --> 00:31:35.351
Bent over backwards twisting it

572
00:31:35.352 --> 00:31:36.436
into some version of
the Fibonacci sequence.

573
00:31:36.437 --> 00:31:38.313
There's nothing there.
Believe me.

574
00:31:38.314 --> 00:31:39.732
Aren't there
12 notes in a scale?

575
00:31:43.777 --> 00:31:45.069
What'd you say?

576
00:31:45.070 --> 00:31:48.197
Music.
My mom was a piano teacher.

577
00:31:48.198 --> 00:31:50.825
She used to say that music
is the universal language.

578
00:31:50.826 --> 00:31:53.077
I mean. there <i>are</i> 12 notes
in a scale. right?

579
00:31:53.078 --> 00:31:55.788
A through G with
the flats and the sharp.

580
00:31:55.789 --> 00:31:58.625
Tea Cup.
you are a fucking genius.

581
00:31:58.626 --> 00:32:00.710
I love you. Uh. we need
to get to the bar.

582
00:32:00.711 --> 00:32:02.170
You need to go to your house.

583
00:32:02.171 --> 00:32:03.379
- Why?
- Victor's mother had a violin.

584
00:32:03.380 --> 00:32:05.131
He hid it somewhere
in your basement.

585
00:32:05.132 --> 00:32:07.091
- Why?
- Because I kept stealing it.

586
00:32:07.092 --> 00:32:09.303
Just meet us at the bar.
Come on. people! Let's go!

587
00:32:17.728 --> 00:32:19.354
- [door closes]
- How's he doing?

588
00:32:19.355 --> 00:32:21.315
I gave him something
that should help him sleep.

589
00:32:23.651 --> 00:32:26.402
Well. what are we gonna
do when he wakes up?

590
00:32:26.403 --> 00:32:28.112
I mean. he tried to...

591
00:32:28.113 --> 00:32:30.782
He had the paddle on his head.

592
00:32:30.783 --> 00:32:31.825
I don't know.

593
00:32:34.662 --> 00:32:39.123
Look. I've...
I've tried to be respectful.

594
00:32:39.124 --> 00:32:41.751
and I've tried
to give you space.

595
00:32:41.752 --> 00:32:43.503
but I just really need you
to talk to me right now.

596
00:32:43.504 --> 00:32:46.422
About what?

597
00:32:46.423 --> 00:32:48.466
Randall just tried
to lobotomize himself.

598
00:32:48.467 --> 00:32:51.762
Julie is a mess. and you're
acting like everything's fine.

599
00:32:52.888 --> 00:32:57.600
Hey. Look. I don't know what
the three of you went through.

600
00:32:57.601 --> 00:32:59.268
but I just need you
to tell me if you're okay.

601
00:32:59.269 --> 00:33:01.104
- Kristi.
- No.

602
00:33:01.105 --> 00:33:02.147
Look at me.

603
00:33:03.232 --> 00:33:05.483
Look at me.

604
00:33:05.484 --> 00:33:07.820
Are you okay?

605
00:33:11.615 --> 00:33:13.617
No. I'm not.

606
00:33:17.413 --> 00:33:19.665
And I don't think any of us
are gonna be.

607
00:33:21.667 --> 00:33:24.210
- Okay.
- Please. can you...

608
00:33:24.211 --> 00:33:25.838
can you tell me
what was in the picture?

609
00:33:27.464 --> 00:33:29.382
Boyd.

610
00:33:29.383 --> 00:33:31.342
What was in the picture?

611
00:33:31.343 --> 00:33:32.719
That's what you wanna know. huh?

612
00:33:32.720 --> 00:33:33.803
Yes. Can... can you just...

613
00:33:33.804 --> 00:33:35.638
[grunting]

614
00:33:35.639 --> 00:33:37.515
Can you tell me
what was in the picture?

615
00:33:37.516 --> 00:33:39.600
You wanna know what was
in the picture. do you?

616
00:33:39.601 --> 00:33:41.519
[laughs bitterly]

617
00:33:41.520 --> 00:33:44.313
You know what was
in the fucking picture?

618
00:33:44.314 --> 00:33:45.773
I'll tell you what was
in the picture.

619
00:33:45.774 --> 00:33:49.819
It was a picture of my house.

620
00:33:49.820 --> 00:33:53.489
the house that I bought
with my wife when I retired.

621
00:33:53.490 --> 00:33:55.950
the one that we were going to

622
00:33:55.951 --> 00:33:59.872
when I ran
into that fucking tree.

623
00:34:01.832 --> 00:34:03.624
The only thing missing

624
00:34:03.625 --> 00:34:05.918
was the boat.

625
00:34:05.919 --> 00:34:07.504
[grunts]

626
00:34:10.674 --> 00:34:12.633
[tools clatter]

627
00:34:12.634 --> 00:34:14.720
Do you see what this means?

628
00:34:18.932 --> 00:34:19.892
She's trying to show you.

629
00:34:21.643 --> 00:34:23.228
We're going home.

630
00:34:24.605 --> 00:34:25.980
All you have to do is wait.

631
00:34:25.981 --> 00:34:27.732
No.

632
00:34:27.733 --> 00:34:30.611
[tools clanking]

633
00:34:33.071 --> 00:34:33.822
Boyd.

634
00:34:35.908 --> 00:34:36.949
Whatever it is
you think you got to do.

635
00:34:36.950 --> 00:34:38.577
you don't have to do it.

636
00:34:40.037 --> 00:34:43.290
I would never. ever hurt Fatima.

637
00:34:45.542 --> 00:34:46.793
[banging]

638
00:34:46.794 --> 00:34:48.753
She's always been kind to me.

639
00:34:48.754 --> 00:34:49.837
[clicking]

640
00:34:49.838 --> 00:34:51.799
Everything I'm doing is for her.

641
00:34:53.675 --> 00:34:54.843
It's to help us.

642
00:34:57.513 --> 00:34:59.722
If you just give it
a little more time...

643
00:34:59.723 --> 00:35:02.267
We don't have any fucking time!

644
00:35:04.478 --> 00:35:06.562
You took my family.

645
00:35:06.563 --> 00:35:08.314
Do you understand that?

646
00:35:08.315 --> 00:35:10.817
You took someone I love.

647
00:35:10.818 --> 00:35:12.735
and you put her in danger.

648
00:35:12.736 --> 00:35:14.779
I'm sorry about
what happened to you.

649
00:35:14.780 --> 00:35:17.573
But we're not gonna wait.
We are not gonna talk.

650
00:35:17.574 --> 00:35:21.953
You're gonna tell me
where she is.

651
00:35:21.954 --> 00:35:24.288
- or I am going to hurt you.
- I can't. I can't.

652
00:35:24.289 --> 00:35:26.332
And I'm not gonna stop
hurting you

653
00:35:26.333 --> 00:35:28.960
until you tell me
what I need to know.

654
00:35:28.961 --> 00:35:30.671
Tell me you understand.

655
00:35:32.631 --> 00:35:34.048
- Tell me!
- I understand.

656
00:35:34.049 --> 00:35:35.591
Good.

657
00:35:35.592 --> 00:35:39.763
[ominous music playing]

658
00:35:43.475 --> 00:35:44.934
Where is she?

659
00:35:44.935 --> 00:35:49.438
[breathing heavily]

660
00:35:49.439 --> 00:35:51.567
Put your hand on the table.

661
00:35:54.444 --> 00:35:56.279
I can't.

662
00:35:56.280 --> 00:35:57.822
Put your hand on the table.

663
00:35:57.823 --> 00:36:00.449
No. please.

664
00:36:00.450 --> 00:36:01.492
No. Boyd. [grunting]

665
00:36:01.493 --> 00:36:02.785
[Boyd] We're playing. are we?

666
00:36:02.786 --> 00:36:03.912
[grunting loudly]

667
00:36:05.539 --> 00:36:07.790
Please. Boyd. Just... just wait.

668
00:36:07.791 --> 00:36:09.584
- Where is she?
- Just...

669
00:36:09.585 --> 00:36:12.378
- It's your last chance.
- I can't. Boyd. I can't.

670
00:36:12.379 --> 00:36:14.964
I can't.

671
00:36:14.965 --> 00:36:18.886
- [Boyd grunting]
- [Elgin shouting. groaning]

672
00:36:20.804 --> 00:36:23.931
Huh?! Where is she?!

673
00:36:23.932 --> 00:36:25.892
[Elgin shouting distantly]

674
00:36:25.893 --> 00:36:27.977
[Boyd] I don't care!
[yelling indistinctly]

675
00:36:27.978 --> 00:36:29.562
[door closes]

676
00:36:29.563 --> 00:36:32.607
Hey. Any news on Fatima?

677
00:36:32.608 --> 00:36:35.568
- [Elgin screaming in distance]
- What the fuck was that?

678
00:36:35.569 --> 00:36:37.486
- [Kenny] Dani. listen...
- [shouting]

679
00:36:37.487 --> 00:36:38.613
[Donna] Hey! No. no. no!
Don't let her get up there!

680
00:36:38.614 --> 00:36:40.114
Dani. you don't understand!

681
00:36:40.115 --> 00:36:42.074
- Please. please. Boyd.
- Huh? Listen!

682
00:36:42.075 --> 00:36:43.576
I'm not playing with you!

683
00:36:43.577 --> 00:36:45.411
Where is she?!

684
00:36:45.412 --> 00:36:47.622
- Jesus.
- [Ellis] Hey!

685
00:36:47.623 --> 00:36:49.665
[sobbing]

686
00:36:49.666 --> 00:36:51.083
What the fuck are you doing?

687
00:36:51.084 --> 00:36:53.711
Turn around
and walk out the door!

688
00:36:53.712 --> 00:36:55.630
- Dani. come on.
- Don't fucking touch me!

689
00:36:55.631 --> 00:36:57.840
Hey. you do not understand
what is going on here!

690
00:36:57.841 --> 00:36:59.634
Then explain it to me.

691
00:36:59.635 --> 00:37:00.801
Everyone downstairs.

692
00:37:00.802 --> 00:37:03.763
- What the...
- [groaning loudly]

693
00:37:03.764 --> 00:37:05.640
- Dad!
- Downstairs!

694
00:37:05.641 --> 00:37:08.559
Let's go.

695
00:37:08.560 --> 00:37:11.604
How do we know
in what order they go in?

696
00:37:11.605 --> 00:37:16.651
Well... we treat it
like any composition.

697
00:37:16.652 --> 00:37:21.073
We try to figure out what is
a chord and what is a melody.

698
00:37:22.866 --> 00:37:25.618
2. 9. 7. 5. 2975.

699
00:37:25.619 --> 00:37:28.080
- The 2 is backwards.
- Mm-hmm.

700
00:37:29.539 --> 00:37:33.084
So. that would be a G

701
00:37:33.085 --> 00:37:35.127
instead of a B. okay.

702
00:37:35.128 --> 00:37:39.715
followed by F sharp. D. E. Okay.

703
00:37:39.716 --> 00:37:42.927
So. if it was a melody.
it would be something like...

704
00:37:42.928 --> 00:37:44.428
<i>♪ Dah dah dah dah ♪</i>

705
00:37:44.429 --> 00:37:47.014
- G. F sharp. E. D.
- Uh-huh.

706
00:37:47.015 --> 00:37:49.100
<i>♪ G. G. another backwards two ♪</i>

707
00:37:49.101 --> 00:37:51.852
<i>♪ G. G. D. C. C ♪</i>

708
00:37:51.853 --> 00:37:53.647
<i>♪ Dah. dah. dah-dah ♪</i>

709
00:37:58.193 --> 00:37:59.945
<i>♪ Dah dah dah dah ♪</i>

710
00:38:02.114 --> 00:38:04.907
[humming]

711
00:38:04.908 --> 00:38:06.200
What's wrong?

712
00:38:06.201 --> 00:38:09.036
[continues humming]

713
00:38:09.037 --> 00:38:11.957
<i>♪ Dah dah dah dah ♪</i>

714
00:38:13.583 --> 00:38:14.792
- D. D.
- [door opens]

715
00:38:14.793 --> 00:38:17.545
[Jade humming]

716
00:38:17.546 --> 00:38:19.088
Found it. How are you
guys coming along?

717
00:38:19.089 --> 00:38:21.090
No. wait. Wait. wait. wait.

718
00:38:21.091 --> 00:38:24.885
<i>♪ Dah dah dah dah dah dah ♪</i>

719
00:38:24.886 --> 00:38:26.513
<i>♪ Dah dah dah ♪</i>

720
00:38:28.974 --> 00:38:30.809
<i>♪ Dah dah dah dah ♪</i>

721
00:38:33.562 --> 00:38:37.064
<i>♪ Dah dah dah ♪</i>

722
00:38:37.065 --> 00:38:39.151
<i>♪ Yah dah dah dah ♪</i>

723
00:38:40.694 --> 00:38:42.737
What is that?

724
00:38:42.738 --> 00:38:45.197
I don't know. I don't know.
I've never heard this before.

725
00:38:45.198 --> 00:38:49.035
I just. um... uh...

726
00:38:49.036 --> 00:38:52.621
I just... I looked
at the numbers.

727
00:38:52.622 --> 00:38:54.874
I looked at the notes.
and I just...

728
00:38:54.875 --> 00:38:57.668
You just what?

729
00:38:57.669 --> 00:38:59.962
I could hear the music.

730
00:38:59.963 --> 00:39:01.797
[gasps]

731
00:39:01.798 --> 00:39:03.549
All right.

732
00:39:03.550 --> 00:39:06.093
<i>♪ Dah dah dah dah ♪</i>

733
00:39:06.094 --> 00:39:06.970
- Wait.
- [Jade singing]

734
00:39:06.971 --> 00:39:08.179
Hey. stop.

735
00:39:08.180 --> 00:39:10.140
What?! What?!

736
00:39:11.725 --> 00:39:13.602
I'm not so sure
this is a good idea.

737
00:39:16.021 --> 00:39:18.147
What are you talking about?

738
00:39:18.148 --> 00:39:19.774
You cracked the code.

739
00:39:19.775 --> 00:39:22.860
Yeah. and the music just
magically popped into your head.

740
00:39:22.861 --> 00:39:25.654
Doesn't that strike you as odd?

741
00:39:25.655 --> 00:39:27.656
Well. I... [chuckles]

742
00:39:27.657 --> 00:39:30.201
Everything about this place
is odd.

743
00:39:30.202 --> 00:39:34.038
And this place is trying
to manipulate us. to hurt us.

744
00:39:34.039 --> 00:39:37.583
Oh. God. Jim. how... how is
playing a song gonna hurt us?

745
00:39:37.584 --> 00:39:39.502
[Jim] Are... are you
forgetting what Boyd said

746
00:39:39.503 --> 00:39:41.837
about the haunted music box

747
00:39:41.838 --> 00:39:43.255
and how it nearly
killed everyone

748
00:39:43.256 --> 00:39:45.174
or... or the...
the jukeboxes in the diner

749
00:39:45.175 --> 00:39:47.176
that just magically
turn on by themselves?

750
00:39:47.177 --> 00:39:48.803
All right. Okay. So. what are
you saying?

751
00:39:48.804 --> 00:39:50.096
We just ignore this?
We forget about it?

752
00:39:50.097 --> 00:39:53.057
No. We can't.

753
00:39:53.058 --> 00:39:56.102
You know. maybe we shouldn't
play it here in town.

754
00:39:56.103 --> 00:39:59.022
just to be safe.
just to make sure.

755
00:40:01.358 --> 00:40:03.275
Well. I don't know if going out
in the woods

756
00:40:03.276 --> 00:40:04.944
is gonna do much good.

757
00:40:04.945 --> 00:40:07.988
I mean. what's the blast radius
on an evil song?

758
00:40:07.989 --> 00:40:10.074
[Tabitha] Well. the message
was left at the tree.

759
00:40:10.075 --> 00:40:11.868
Maybe we should play it there.

760
00:40:14.663 --> 00:40:18.874
[Fatima breathing heavily]

761
00:40:18.875 --> 00:40:19.917
[grunting]

762
00:40:19.918 --> 00:40:24.880
[breathing heavily]

763
00:40:24.881 --> 00:40:26.924
[ominous music playing]

764
00:40:26.925 --> 00:40:29.928
♪

765
00:40:38.895 --> 00:40:39.813
[groaning]

766
00:40:41.815 --> 00:40:43.150
[gasps]

767
00:40:45.819 --> 00:40:47.194
- [female voice] <i>Stop!</i>
- [gasping]

768
00:40:47.195 --> 00:40:51.616
[breathing heavily]

769
00:40:52.742 --> 00:40:56.788
No. no. no. no. no. no.

770
00:40:59.082 --> 00:41:00.249
It's coming.

771
00:41:00.250 --> 00:41:03.127
[splattering]

772
00:41:03.128 --> 00:41:07.090
[breathing heavily]

773
00:41:08.675 --> 00:41:11.303
[indistinct conversations]

774
00:41:17.184 --> 00:41:20.728
What if we forget what
she was like?

775
00:41:20.729 --> 00:41:21.729
What?

776
00:41:21.730 --> 00:41:23.939
Tian-Chen.

777
00:41:23.940 --> 00:41:26.859
I don't wanna forget
what she was like.

778
00:41:26.860 --> 00:41:28.777
You won't.

779
00:41:28.778 --> 00:41:29.988
Why would you think that?

780
00:41:33.158 --> 00:41:35.911
Because I'm starting to
forget what Thomas was like.

781
00:41:50.050 --> 00:41:51.343
I have to tell you something.

782
00:41:54.054 --> 00:41:56.889
When we went to those ruins.

783
00:41:56.890 --> 00:42:00.684
when I walked inside. I...

784
00:42:00.685 --> 00:42:02.228
I didn't just have a dream.

785
00:42:02.229 --> 00:42:04.356
I think I went somewhere.

786
00:42:05.982 --> 00:42:07.066
What do you mean?

787
00:42:07.067 --> 00:42:08.944
I don't know how. but I...

788
00:42:10.278 --> 00:42:12.821
When we went to the ruins.

789
00:42:12.822 --> 00:42:14.783
suddenly I was in a chamber.

790
00:42:16.326 --> 00:42:18.077
And I saw me
and Randall and Marielle

791
00:42:18.078 --> 00:42:19.871
chained to the wall.

792
00:42:21.289 --> 00:42:22.998
What were you doing?

793
00:42:22.999 --> 00:42:25.042
We were screaming.

794
00:42:25.043 --> 00:42:27.420
I think that's where we were
when we couldn't wake up.

795
00:42:31.174 --> 00:42:32.758
But then I left the chamber.

796
00:42:32.759 --> 00:42:34.343
and I went into the tunnels.

797
00:42:34.344 --> 00:42:36.428
I heard Mom's voice.

798
00:42:36.429 --> 00:42:38.138
And she was talking to Victor.

799
00:42:38.139 --> 00:42:40.391
Remember how she said
that Victor was the one

800
00:42:40.392 --> 00:42:42.434
who helped her find her way
out of the tunnels

801
00:42:42.435 --> 00:42:44.103
that night when the house
fell down?

802
00:42:44.104 --> 00:42:45.896
I think that's what I heard.

803
00:42:45.897 --> 00:42:48.899
but I think
I was actually there.

804
00:42:48.900 --> 00:42:52.404
like... like I somehow
went back to that night.

805
00:42:53.822 --> 00:42:55.447
You're a Storywalker.

806
00:42:55.448 --> 00:42:56.908
What?

807
00:42:58.410 --> 00:43:00.202
Someone who can visit

808
00:43:00.203 --> 00:43:02.871
chapters of the story
that already happened.

809
00:43:02.872 --> 00:43:04.749
What...

810
00:43:06.459 --> 00:43:07.876
So. I go back to those ruins.

811
00:43:07.877 --> 00:43:10.213
do you... do you think
I could do it again?

812
00:43:12.173 --> 00:43:14.133
Maybe. Why?

813
00:43:14.134 --> 00:43:15.468
Well. if...

814
00:43:18.555 --> 00:43:21.181
[lowered voice] ...this is real.

815
00:43:21.182 --> 00:43:22.934
that means I can change things.

816
00:43:24.394 --> 00:43:26.812
I can save Tian-Chen.

817
00:43:26.813 --> 00:43:28.188
Maybe I could even save Thomas.

818
00:43:28.189 --> 00:43:30.899
Mm. it doesn't work like that.

819
00:43:30.900 --> 00:43:33.944
- But you just said...
- You can visit the chapters.

820
00:43:33.945 --> 00:43:35.822
But you can't change them.

821
00:43:36.948 --> 00:43:38.282
Why?

822
00:43:38.283 --> 00:43:41.411
No one can change a story
once it's been told.

823
00:43:44.831 --> 00:43:46.165
It is not what it looks like.

824
00:43:46.166 --> 00:43:49.209
No? Because it looked like
you were torturing that kid.

825
00:43:49.210 --> 00:43:52.755
- You're really okay with this?
- He knows where Fatima is.

826
00:43:52.756 --> 00:43:54.965
Look. I get that you wanna
find her. Okay? I do.

827
00:43:54.966 --> 00:43:57.384
But there is a right
and a wrong way to do this.

828
00:43:57.385 --> 00:43:59.094
[Boyd] Tell me the right way.

829
00:43:59.095 --> 00:44:01.305
You got all the answers! Tell
me the right way to do this!

830
00:44:01.306 --> 00:44:03.182
[Dani] I don't know.
but maybe something

831
00:44:03.183 --> 00:44:05.142
that doesn't involve
torturing a scared kid.

832
00:44:05.143 --> 00:44:08.146
[sobbing]

833
00:44:17.864 --> 00:44:19.324
Sara.

834
00:44:26.289 --> 00:44:27.414
Hi. Elgin.

835
00:44:27.415 --> 00:44:30.835
[crying]

836
00:44:33.254 --> 00:44:36.465
I'd tell you if I could.
but... I can't.

837
00:44:36.466 --> 00:44:38.510
It's okay.

838
00:44:40.261 --> 00:44:41.261
I understand.

839
00:44:41.262 --> 00:44:43.472
That first day.

840
00:44:43.473 --> 00:44:48.477
when I saw you in the church.

841
00:44:48.478 --> 00:44:51.480
my heart broke for you.

842
00:44:51.481 --> 00:44:56.985
I thought. "He seems so sweet.

843
00:44:56.986 --> 00:44:58.362
so kind."

844
00:44:58.363 --> 00:44:59.280
[groans softly]

845
00:44:59.281 --> 00:45:02.116
I was like that once.

846
00:45:02.117 --> 00:45:05.369
I think...

847
00:45:05.370 --> 00:45:08.373
maybe we're exactly what
this place looks for.

848
00:45:10.125 --> 00:45:11.333
No.

849
00:45:11.334 --> 00:45:13.002
People who just want to help.

850
00:45:14.546 --> 00:45:19.007
Sara. can you please
tell Boyd to stop?

851
00:45:19.008 --> 00:45:20.551
He'll listen to you.

852
00:45:20.552 --> 00:45:25.180
If we just wait
a little longer...

853
00:45:25.181 --> 00:45:26.974
Then Fatima could die.

854
00:45:26.975 --> 00:45:28.976
- No! She's not... Sara. no!
- Yes! Yes!

855
00:45:28.977 --> 00:45:30.853
I know you don't believe that.

856
00:45:30.854 --> 00:45:33.272
I know that you think
that you're saving everyone.

857
00:45:33.273 --> 00:45:35.233
Sara. please!

858
00:45:41.448 --> 00:45:45.075
[Elgin groaning. crying]

859
00:45:45.076 --> 00:45:47.327
Boyd doesn't understand

860
00:45:47.328 --> 00:45:50.205
how far he needs to go
to make you tell him.

861
00:45:50.206 --> 00:45:52.208
[crying]

862
00:45:55.962 --> 00:45:57.045
Don't...

863
00:45:57.046 --> 00:45:59.882
[ominous music playing]

864
00:45:59.883 --> 00:46:02.176
He's a good man.

865
00:46:02.177 --> 00:46:04.470
And this place.

866
00:46:04.471 --> 00:46:07.140
it's taken so much from him.

867
00:46:10.101 --> 00:46:11.311
I won't let it take his soul.

868
00:46:15.064 --> 00:46:15.982
Sara.

869
00:46:15.983 --> 00:46:19.234
I've already given it mine.

870
00:46:19.235 --> 00:46:21.987
This is not Camden!
I'm not debating this with you!

871
00:46:21.988 --> 00:46:23.906
It's happening!
You got a problem?

872
00:46:23.907 --> 00:46:26.366
Take it up with me
after Fatima is safe!

873
00:46:26.367 --> 00:46:29.328
- Is this what you mean by trust?
- Yeah.

874
00:46:29.329 --> 00:46:31.413
Okay. How's it gonna play
when I go and tell everyone

875
00:46:31.414 --> 00:46:33.248
- what you're doing?
- Are you...

876
00:46:33.249 --> 00:46:35.542
- [Elgin yelling in distance]
- Shit.

877
00:46:35.543 --> 00:46:36.919
Go!

878
00:46:36.920 --> 00:46:41.924
[Elgin screaming]

879
00:46:41.925 --> 00:46:44.218
[screams continuing]

880
00:46:44.219 --> 00:46:45.385
[Boyd] Sara?

881
00:46:45.386 --> 00:46:49.431
[Elgin sobbing]

882
00:46:49.432 --> 00:46:50.516
Hey. Sara.

883
00:46:50.517 --> 00:46:52.935
[Elgin crying]

884
00:46:52.936 --> 00:46:55.939
[whimpering]

885
00:46:59.359 --> 00:47:00.485
Sara. what...

886
00:47:02.278 --> 00:47:05.365
She's in the root cellar.

887
00:47:06.783 --> 00:47:09.201
If anyone's having
second thoughts.

888
00:47:09.202 --> 00:47:12.956
speak now
or forever hold your peace.

889
00:47:16.417 --> 00:47:17.502
Go ahead.

890
00:47:22.173 --> 00:47:25.425
[playing seven notes]

891
00:47:25.426 --> 00:47:28.388
♪

892
00:47:33.726 --> 00:47:36.353
[playing seven different notes]

893
00:47:36.354 --> 00:47:39.274
♪

894
00:47:44.737 --> 00:47:50.409
[playing first set of notes]

895
00:47:50.410 --> 00:47:54.746
[screaming in pain]

896
00:47:54.747 --> 00:47:59.293
[second set of notes playing]

897
00:47:59.294 --> 00:48:01.713
[Fatima continues screaming]

898
00:48:07.677 --> 00:48:10.512
[playing first set of notes]

899
00:48:10.513 --> 00:48:12.514
♪

900
00:48:12.515 --> 00:48:15.434
[playing second set of notes]

901
00:48:15.435 --> 00:48:21.773
♪

902
00:48:21.774 --> 00:48:24.109
[screaming]

903
00:48:24.110 --> 00:48:29.531
[Fatima screaming. muffled]

904
00:48:29.532 --> 00:48:32.452
[continues screaming]

905
00:48:34.579 --> 00:48:36.538
[continues screaming]

906
00:48:36.539 --> 00:48:40.751
[panting]

907
00:48:40.752 --> 00:48:42.753
[grunting]

908
00:48:42.754 --> 00:48:46.173
[Fatima panting]

909
00:48:46.174 --> 00:48:47.674
[grunting]

910
00:48:47.675 --> 00:48:50.595
[dramatic music playing]

911
00:48:52.263 --> 00:48:54.556
[rumbling outside]

912
00:48:54.557 --> 00:48:57.184
- [door unlocks]
- [grunting]

913
00:48:57.185 --> 00:48:58.144
Fatima! Hey.

914
00:48:58.145 --> 00:49:01.855
Hey. I'm here. I'm here.

915
00:49:01.856 --> 00:49:04.733
[all panting]

916
00:49:04.734 --> 00:49:05.859
She took it. [crying]

917
00:49:05.860 --> 00:49:07.320
What?

918
00:49:08.613 --> 00:49:10.697
She... she... she took it.

919
00:49:10.698 --> 00:49:14.701
The... the thing.
she... she took it down there.

920
00:49:14.702 --> 00:49:17.329
It's okay. It's okay.

921
00:49:17.330 --> 00:49:19.206
It's okay now.

922
00:49:19.207 --> 00:49:21.167
We're gonna get you out of here.

923
00:49:22.377 --> 00:49:23.585
Dad?

924
00:49:23.586 --> 00:49:26.463
You and Kenny get her back
to Colony House.

925
00:49:26.464 --> 00:49:27.673
What?

926
00:49:27.674 --> 00:49:30.092
- I need to see it.
- Boyd. we...

927
00:49:30.093 --> 00:49:31.468
Look.
Whatever this is.

928
00:49:31.469 --> 00:49:33.595
I'm not gonna be blindsided
by this place again.

929
00:49:33.596 --> 00:49:34.888
No. Dad. what are you...
You can't...

930
00:49:34.889 --> 00:49:37.141
Look. Go.
Take care of your wife.

931
00:49:38.559 --> 00:49:41.770
I'll be right behind you. okay?

932
00:49:41.771 --> 00:49:44.773
♪

933
00:49:44.774 --> 00:49:47.610
[score playing Jade's melody]

934
00:50:03.501 --> 00:50:06.337
[playing longer melody]

935
00:50:20.727 --> 00:50:22.562
They're here.

936
00:50:24.522 --> 00:50:27.190
What? Where?

937
00:50:27.191 --> 00:50:29.193
[crows cawing distantly]

938
00:50:36.868 --> 00:50:38.493
Do you see them?

939
00:50:38.494 --> 00:50:43.915
[dramatic music playing]

940
00:50:43.916 --> 00:50:47.169
Come on. Keep playing.
Keep playing.

941
00:50:47.170 --> 00:50:49.963
[playing longer melody]

942
00:50:49.964 --> 00:50:52.925
♪

943
00:51:05.938 --> 00:51:09.233
[score playing Jade's melody]

944
00:51:18.367 --> 00:51:19.493
- You're okay.
- [whimpering]

945
00:51:19.494 --> 00:51:21.203
You're okay.

946
00:51:21.204 --> 00:51:24.248
No. Ellis. I-I-I saw them.

947
00:51:25.666 --> 00:51:27.959
I saw what they did.

948
00:51:27.960 --> 00:51:30.295
- What?
- Those things

949
00:51:30.296 --> 00:51:31.463
that come out at night.

950
00:51:31.464 --> 00:51:33.257
I saw what they are.

951
00:51:35.676 --> 00:51:39.387
They sacrificed
their... their children.

952
00:51:39.388 --> 00:51:43.559
because It promised them that
they would live forever.

953
00:51:45.019 --> 00:51:48.272
♪

954
00:52:00.910 --> 00:52:03.746
♪

955
00:53:22.617 --> 00:53:23.784
Anghkooey.

956
00:53:34.170 --> 00:53:35.796
Remember.

957
00:53:38.090 --> 00:53:40.801
- What's that?
- Anghkooey.

958
00:53:42.094 --> 00:53:44.889
It means "remember."

959
00:53:48.601 --> 00:53:49.601
[crying]

960
00:53:49.602 --> 00:53:52.520
- We tried to save them...
- No.

961
00:53:52.521 --> 00:53:54.689
- ...because one of them...
- No. no. no. no.

962
00:53:54.690 --> 00:53:56.567
Oh. God.

963
00:53:59.111 --> 00:54:02.364
No. no. no. I can't.
I can't. I can't.

964
00:54:02.365 --> 00:54:03.532
What just happened?

965
00:54:08.955 --> 00:54:10.915
We used to sing them lullabies.

966
00:54:21.968 --> 00:54:23.176
Tabitha.

967
00:54:23.177 --> 00:54:24.719
- No. I can't.
- Hey. Hey.

968
00:54:24.720 --> 00:54:26.555
- No. no. no. no. no. I can't.
- Tab...

969
00:54:29.141 --> 00:54:30.142
You can't?

970
00:54:32.603 --> 00:54:35.022
- Please. talk to me.
- I know why.

971
00:54:36.273 --> 00:54:39.150
I know why I see those children.

972
00:54:39.151 --> 00:54:42.154
- Okay.
- Why Jade can see them.

973
00:54:45.658 --> 00:54:47.576
It's why there's more
than one bracelet.

974
00:54:48.995 --> 00:54:50.121
I kept making them.

975
00:54:52.123 --> 00:54:54.165
Somewhere deep down. I remember.

976
00:54:54.166 --> 00:54:55.418
[crying]

977
00:54:56.794 --> 00:54:59.588
I-I don't know what
the fuck you're saying!

978
00:55:01.090 --> 00:55:02.466
I don't understand.

979
00:55:07.179 --> 00:55:09.097
It's because
we've been here before.

980
00:55:09.098 --> 00:55:10.933
me and Jade.

981
00:55:12.935 --> 00:55:16.855
The reason I
felt what Miranda felt

982
00:55:16.856 --> 00:55:18.482
is because I was Miranda.

983
00:55:22.570 --> 00:55:27.158
And Jade...
Jade was Christopher.

984
00:55:28.909 --> 00:55:30.952
We've come back
over and over again

985
00:55:30.953 --> 00:55:33.456
because we failed
the first time.

986
00:55:34.582 --> 00:55:37.208
- The first time?
- Yes.

987
00:55:37.209 --> 00:55:40.129
Jade and I were here
at the beginning.

988
00:55:42.798 --> 00:55:44.925
We tried to save those
children and set them free...

989
00:55:49.555 --> 00:55:51.807
...because one of them
was ours.

990
00:55:53.601 --> 00:55:55.560
[sobbing]

991
00:55:55.561 --> 00:55:57.187
She was our daughter.

992
00:55:57.188 --> 00:56:02.067
No. No. that's not...

993
00:56:02.068 --> 00:56:04.820
It's true.
It's true. I feel it.

994
00:56:08.074 --> 00:56:09.241
And I need some time. honey.

995
00:56:11.660 --> 00:56:13.161
Can you give me some time?

996
00:56:13.162 --> 00:56:14.871
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

997
00:56:14.872 --> 00:56:17.833
[dramatic music playing]

998
00:56:29.261 --> 00:56:30.678
[Jim] Sometimes I
remember what it was like

999
00:56:30.679 --> 00:56:34.140
when it wasn't like this.

1000
00:56:34.141 --> 00:56:37.685
what it was like before.

1001
00:56:37.686 --> 00:56:40.605
[pensive music playing]

1002
00:56:40.606 --> 00:56:43.567
♪

1003
00:57:07.424 --> 00:57:10.593
[Julie] Dad!
Can you hear me?!

1004
00:57:10.594 --> 00:57:12.679
- Julie?!
- Dad!

1005
00:57:12.680 --> 00:57:14.056
I'm over here!

1006
00:57:15.224 --> 00:57:16.142
Over here!

1007
00:57:19.687 --> 00:57:21.938
Dad! Dad. you have to run!

1008
00:57:21.939 --> 00:57:23.815
You need to get
to town right now!

1009
00:57:23.816 --> 00:57:25.233
- What's happened to you?
- You need to listen to me!

1010
00:57:25.234 --> 00:57:27.652
It's not safe! I don't...
I think this is when it happens!

1011
00:57:27.653 --> 00:57:29.988
- Okay. Slow down. We're okay.
- No. no. Listen to me.

1012
00:57:29.989 --> 00:57:31.364
- It's okay.
- I need to change the story.

1013
00:57:31.365 --> 00:57:32.324
- Dad. please!
- All right.

1014
00:57:32.325 --> 00:57:34.659
That was a hell of a song.

1015
00:57:34.660 --> 00:57:36.327
[ominous music playing]

1016
00:57:36.328 --> 00:57:39.290
♪

1017
00:57:45.171 --> 00:57:47.339
That Jade sure can play.

1018
00:57:50.342 --> 00:57:52.135
- Get outta here. Run.
- No. you don't understand.

1019
00:57:52.136 --> 00:57:53.345
Run. Run.

1020
00:57:55.347 --> 00:57:57.140
This didn't have to
happen. you know.

1021
00:57:57.141 --> 00:57:58.349
Back up.

1022
00:57:58.350 --> 00:58:01.102
Knowledge comes with a cost.

1023
00:58:01.103 --> 00:58:03.897
I said back the fuck up!

1024
00:58:03.898 --> 00:58:05.232
Dad. please!

1025
00:58:06.984 --> 00:58:07.943
Dad. please!

1026
00:58:07.944 --> 00:58:09.277
I did try to warn you.

1027
00:58:09.278 --> 00:58:10.613
[grunting]

1028
00:58:11.780 --> 00:58:13.740
[gasping]

1029
00:58:13.741 --> 00:58:14.783
[banging]

1030
00:58:16.035 --> 00:58:18.828
Get off him!

1031
00:58:18.829 --> 00:58:20.998
[grunting]

1032
00:58:23.000 --> 00:58:25.252
Your wife shouldn't have
dug that hole. Jim.

1033
00:58:27.504 --> 00:58:29.714
[gasping]

1034
00:58:29.715 --> 00:58:31.926
No!

1035
00:58:34.136 --> 00:58:37.014
♪
